<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Which of the following best demonstrates the concept of crowding out in fiscal policy?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Government spending increases total GDP</option>
            <option letter="b">Government borrowing raises interest rates, reducing private investment</option>
            <option letter="c">Tax increases reduce consumer spending</option>
            <option letter="d">Inflation reduces purchasing power</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Crowding out occurs when increased government borrowing drives up interest rates in the loanable funds market. These higher rates make it more expensive for private businesses to borrow and invest, thus "crowding out" private investment that would have otherwise occurred.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
